<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. waisaliensis" pageId="4" pageNumber="89" rank="species" species="waisaliensis">C. waisaliensis</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., but differs in its axillary cyme inflorescence of 2-4 flowers (vs. cauliflorous cyme inflorescence of 2-8 flowers), green bracts and bracteoles 5-9 mm long (vs. white bracts and bracteoles 3-10 mm long), calyx pale green and 29-31 mm long (vs. calyx white and 23-37 mm long), corolla tube 31-34 mm long (vs. corolla tube 23-27 mm long), and staminodes 2 (vs. staminodes 3).
</paragraph>
